Two persons on Monday escaped by whiskers when a bus carrying them suddenly went up in flames in Igboukwu, Aguata Local Government Area of Anambra. The bus loaded with diesel reportedly crashed and spilled its contents before it was further by fire. The Nation gathered the occupants, the driver and his conductor, quickly jumped out of the vehicle before it was razed. The Ag. Public Education Officer, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Kamal Musa confirmed the incident, saying no life was lost. He said: “A ford bus laden with diesel in containers crashed and caught fire at Igboukwu. No life was lost.
Details in due course.”